i will be more than happy to give rsgp as a reward if you guys cannot help for free then i understand …

add me on skype: ( mamali.tahamtan ) (canada) or msn: ( mamalibbm@hotmail.com ) to contact me please or just comment below thankyou very much

When your portfowarding threw your modem, do you have the TCP/UDP on both, or do you have one separate portfoward for each?

Also go to canyouseeme.org and see if it works on your port, and on top of that run your server, and then do it again to see if it opened the port.[/quote]
Never use canyouseeme.org. That site only says if a port is open when something is broadcasting on the open port.
Let me find a link real fast.

Edit: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,590760.0.html
That should help.

item.title: Portforwarding error (43594) cannot portforward , please help!?
item.dc:creator: @malimt malimt
item.description:
@malimt wrote:

Creative I:

idk what you mean at this point … ,

Okay let me brake it down for you:

Have the TCP/UDP on different ports on 43594.
Then dont portfoward using the 192.0.0.1 (Your IP …).
When you go to canyouseeme.org, use that given IP to portfoward.
Also canyouseeme.org will not catch your port, unless you have your server running.
Also when you have all that dealt with, make sure that you allow the port threw your firewall.
Also for that make sure you have 2 different exceptions threw firewall both TCP & UDP.
Have it your server name and put running on port 43594.
Then on canyouseeme.org should catch everything perfectly.
[/quote] didnt work but i managed to find the problem i just had to enable port triggering … thnx tho
